  "text": "The major kubelet components owned by sig-node are implemented in the following Go source files in kubernetes/kubernetes:\n\n1. **Pod Lifecycle Manager** (pkg/kubelet/pod/pod_manager.go): Manages pod state mappings between static pods and mirror pods. The Manager interface is the public API, with basicManager providing the implementation. This component tracks pods admitted to the kubelet and coordinates with mirror pods in the API server.\n\n2. **Container Runtime Interface (CRI) Client** (pkg/kubelet/container/runtime.go): Defines the Runtime interface that abstracts the container runtime implementation. This serves as the main interface for all container operations (create, start, stop, delete, etc.). It uses the CRI API (k8s.io/cri-api/pkg/apis) to communicate with container runtimes.\n\n3. **Pod Lifecycle Event Generator (PLEG)** (pkg/kubelet/pleg/pleg.go, generic.go): The PodLifecycleEventGenerator interface generates events for pod/container state changes. The GenericPLEG implementation in generic.go provides polling-based event detection, detecting changes through periodic relisting of containers. This is critical for pod synchronization as it notifies the kubelet when containers are created, started, or terminated.\n\n4. **KubeRuntime Manager** (pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go): The kubeGenericRuntimeManager implements the Runtime interface and serves as the CRI client. Created via NewKubeGenericRuntimeManager(), it handles all pod lifecycle operations by calling the CRI API through runtimeService. This manager orchestrates container creation, configuration setup, and lifecycle hooks.\n\n5. **Volume Manager** (pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/volume_manager.go): The VolumeManager interface defines attachment and mounting operations for volumes. It runs asynchronous loops to reconcile the desired state (pods with volume references) with the actual state (mounted volumes), handling attach, mount, unmount, and detach operations.\n\n6. **Device Plugin Manager** (pkg/kubelet/pluginmanager/plugin_manager.go): The PluginManager interface manages device and plugin registration/deregistration. The pluginManager implementation (created via NewPluginManager) runs asynchronous loops using a reconciler pattern to track plugin state and trigger registration/deregistration operations. This is critical for GPU, device, and other plugin integrations.\n\nAll these components are located in pkg/kubelet and its subdirectories, with ownership confirmed in the OWNERS file under sig-node-approvers and sig-node-reviewers."
}

